ident of France, said on Monday in an interview with French outlets BFM TV and RMC that the opening ceremony could relocate to an indoor location \\\"depending on our analysis of the context.\\\"\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 513, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 299, \"end\": 314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 333, \"end\": 339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999976342550271, \"rank\": 2.059738717870164e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 392, \"end\": 398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BFM_TV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BFM TV\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BFM_TV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BFM_TV\"}, {\"begin\": 403, \"end\": 406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_Monte_Carlo\", \"score\": 0.9999805897817867, \"rank\": 1.9410588948808805e-05, \"text\": \"RMC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_Monte_Carlo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_Monte_Carlo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the president\", \"from\": 316, \"to\": 329}, {\"ngram\": \"Monday\", \"from\": 349, \"to\": 355}, {\"ngram\": \"an interview\", \"from\": 359, \"to\": 371}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 412, \"to\": 432}, {\"ngram\": \"an indoor location\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 469}, {\"ngram\": \"our analysis\", \"from\": 484, \"to\": 496}, {\"ngram\": \"the context\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 511}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have fallback scenarios.\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 542, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fallback scenarios\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 541}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are plan Bs and plan Cs,\\\" Macron said, citing the Stade de France as an alternate location.Related Stories'Four More Shots Please!'\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 680, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 575, \"end\": 581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9075288303009437e-20, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"plan\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 557}, {\"ngram\": \"Bs\", \"from\": 558, \"to\": 560}, {\"ngram\": \"the Stade de France\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 614}, {\"ngram\": \"an alternate location\", \"from\": 618, \"to\": 639}, {\"ngram\": \"More Shots\", \"from\": 661, \"to\": 671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sets Final Season Date on Prime Video (EXCLUSIVE)Manoj Bajpayee's 'The Family Man' Season 3 Becomes Prime Video India's Most-Watched Series of 2025 (EXCLUSIVE) Under the current plans put together by Tony Estanguet, the gold-medal winning French athlete who presides over the Paris 2024 Summer Olympics, as many as 10,500 athletes from all around the world will parade on boats along the six-kilometer Seine River.\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 1096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 882, \"end\": 896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sets Final Season Date\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 703}, {\"ngram\": \"Prime Video\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 718}, {\"ngram\": \"EXCLUSIVE)Manoj\", \"from\": 720, \"to\": 735}, {\"ngram\": \"Prime Video India's Most-Watched Series\", \"from\": 781, \"to\": 820}, {\"ngram\": \"EXCLUSIVE\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 839}, {\"ngram\": \"the current plans\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 864}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold-medal winning French athlete\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 934}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 962}, {\"ngram\": \"Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 983}, {\"ngram\": \"as many as 10,500 athletes\", \"from\": 985, \"to\": 1011}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"boats\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1058}, {\"ngram\": \"the six-kilometer Seine River\", \"from\": 1065, \"to\": 1094}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Macron suggested the itinerary might be shortened.\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1097, \"end\": 1103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9075288303009437e-20, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the itinerary\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1127}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Original plans have already been downsized by French Interior minister Gerald Darmanin who said in January that the ceremony will be accessible to a crowd of approximately 300,000 spectators instead of the 600,000 people initially envisioned.Popular on Variety Estanguet, meanwhile, says he still has faith that the opening ceremony will unspool along the Seine and emphasizes that the Olympics will be organized under an unprecedented security protocol that has been in the works for over four years.\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1194, \"end\": 1218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\", \"score\": 0.9999999999108695, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Interior minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\"}, {\"begin\": 1219, \"end\": 1225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\", \"score\": 0.9999989602875705, \"rank\": 9.95968546416487e-07, \"text\": \"Gerald\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\"}, {\"begin\": 1401, \"end\": 1408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Variety_show\", \"score\": 0.9999993079200188, \"rank\": 6.920586072669682e-07, \"text\": \"Variety\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Variety_show\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Variety_show\"}, {\"begin\": 1505, \"end\": 1510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999996782662, \"rank\": 3.216796417680848e-10, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Original plans\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1162}, {\"ngram\": \"January\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1254}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1272}, {\"ngram\": \"a crowd\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1302}, {\"ngram\": \"approximately 300,000 spectators\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1338}, {\"ngram\": \"the 600,000 people\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1368}, {\"ngram\": \"Popular\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1397}, {\"ngram\": \"faith\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1454}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1480}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1542}, {\"ngram\": \"an unprecedented security protocol\", \"from\": 1567, \"to\": 1601}, {\"ngram\": \"the works\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1628}, {\"ngram\": \"over four years\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1648}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will involve tens of thousands of police and military forces, along with private security.\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\": 1744, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"tens of thousands\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1684}, {\"ngram\": \"police\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1694}, {\"ngram\": \"military forces\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1714}, {\"ngram\": \"private security\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1743}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There will be more than 2,000 private security agents and 45,000 security forces, as well as state services who will ensure waterway and aerial security.\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1898, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more than 2,000 private security agents\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1798}, {\"ngram\": \"45,000 security forces\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1825}, {\"ngram\": \"state services\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1852}, {\"ngram\": \"waterway and aerial security\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 1897}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Referring to eventual fallback plans, Estanguet said some \\\"contingency plans\\\" were being prepared, notably one that would see the opening ceremony confined to the Trocadero area.\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 2078, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2063, \"end\": 2072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trocadero\", \"score\": 0.9985090689830288, \"rank\": 0.0014931541752920272, \"text\": \"Trocadero\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trocadero\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trocadero\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"eventual fallback plans\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1936}, {\"ngram\": \"Estanguet\", \"from\": 1938, \"to\": 1947}, {\"ngram\": \"some \\\"contingency plans\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 1976}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2046}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the worst-case scenario, Estanguet said the Stade de France, a national stadium located just north of Paris, could potentially host the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2184, \"end\": 2189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8182194530255336e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the worst-case scenario\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2105}, {\"ngram\": \"Estanguet\", \"from\": 2107, \"to\": 2116}, {\"ngram\": \"the Stade de France\", \"from\": 2122, \"to\": 2141}, {\"ngram\": \"a national stadium\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2161}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2214, \"to\": 2234}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In an interview withVariety, Estanguet said \\\"France submitted a bid to host these Olympics a few months after the 2015 Paris attacks to defend its ideals of freedom and fraternity in dark times.\\\"\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2282, \"end\": 2288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999976342550271, \"rank\": 2.059738717870164e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an interview withVariety\", \"from\": 2240, \"to\": 2264}, {\"ngram\": \"Estanguet\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2275}, {\"ngram\": \"a bid\", \"from\": 2299, \"to\": 2304}, {\"ngram\": \"these Olympics\", \"from\": 2313, \"to\": 2327}, {\"ngram\": \"its ideals\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2390}, {\"ngram\": \"freedom\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2401}, {\"ngram\": \"fraternity\", \"from\": 2406, \"to\": 2416}, {\"ngram\": \"dark times\", \"from\": 2420, \"to\": 2430}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was our way of showing our faith in the future and now it's time to celebrate what we have achieved,\\\" Estanguet said.\", \"from\": 2434, \"to\": 2555, \"entities\": [], \"noun_p